description: B20 Biodiesel is a blend of 20% biodiesel and 80% petroleum diesel
It is a domestically produced, renewable fuel that can be manufactured from vegetable oils, animal fats, or recycled restaurant grease for use in diesel vehicles.
It is a fuel which can be used in place of gasoline, diesel fuel and LPG. CNG combustion produces fewer undesirable gases.
Diesel fuel is a mixture of hydrocarbons obtained by distillation of crude oil
E10 is regular unleaded petrol blended with between 9% and 10% ethanol. E10 is a safe and reliable fuel.
E25 contains 25% ethanol. These blends have been widely used in Brazil since the late 1970s
It contains high-level ethanol-gasoline blends containing 51% to 83% ethanol, depending on geography and season. It can be used in flexible fuel vehicles
Ethanol fuel is ethyl alcohol, the same type of alcohol found in alcoholic beverages, used as fuel
Gasoline is a colorless petroleum-derived flammable liquid that is used primarily as a fuel in spark-ignited internal combustion engines
Liquefied petroleum gas is a flammable mixture of hydrocarbon gases used as fuel in heating appliances, cooking equipment, and vehicles
Petroleum is a naturally occurring, yellowish-black liquid found in geological formations beneath the Earth's surface
